<br>
The description is in Sony's book describing every class.  It does say that Nukes is only bested by Wizards.  It even says we can call up powerful elementals to fight for us. It says we are self reliant because we can summon.  It did not say that was our main focus.  That is where the disagreements with Magicians come into play.  If you take 10 different people that read the same thing you will probably get 10 different answers.  <br>
<br>
A Magician power lies in his Nukes and Pet.  Verant once said that is the reason we have no defensive ability.  We summon no barrier to protect us, we cannot root, snare, feign death, etc.  A Magician is purely offensive.  Our Pets with our Nukes = Wizard offensive power.  At one time we were higher damage dealers then them.  To a degree we still are, because we can sustain our damage.  I ask Magicians to not lose sight of how they got to level 50, it was not just summoning because that was not all you were about.  We were &quot;Best Soloing&quot; class.  How do you get to be that if it werent for damage dealing?  Or if you were only summoning?<br>
<br>
Also, we are suppose to be &quot;Master of Elements&quot;.  Not druids.  We should be able to control all elements.  For example:  How able a Air based Nuke (Air)?  Or a Earthquake to AE (earth)?  Water based Nuke that restricts breathing (water)?  We have our Fire nukes.  Those might be far fetched, but why cant we have something like those as damage dealing.  They represent the pets we call forth and would give us something that no other class have.  Oh well, Im back to EQ.<br>
<br>
Immlazen<br>
Arch Mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uarchangyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Archangyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(9/18/02 11:47:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fantasygamer.net/ff9/artwork/bomb.jpg  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Really want class balance ?  </span><hr size=1> Wanna be master of elements? How bout:<br>
