<br>
A magician's power comes from a complete understanding on how his or her class works.  Our &quot;hot spot&quot; changes as we level.  Every class in the game that casts spells has some kind of dd's and/or DoTs, so that really isn't our most distinguishing feature.  Our damage comes from a combination of pets, nukes, damage shields, focus items, and pet buffs.  The whole package is the important thing, from the summons to the nukes, and everything in between.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> We were &quot;Best Soloing&quot; class.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I never heard any reference to magicians being the &quot;best&quot; soloers.  Druids and necromancers generally best a magician's efforts, particularly in the formative levels.  We have a unique flavor, however.  We were forced to improvise strategies to make up for our shortcomings, allowing us to shine in our own unique ways.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Also, we are suppose to be &quot;Master of Elements&quot;. Not druids.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is our title.  The truth, however, is obviously different.  Verant never envisioned water based, air based, or earth based spells for our use.  They gave those abilities to our summons.  Our more proper title would probably be conjurer, despite the other labels.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now for some biased opinions:  I have never felt a need for cold based spells in my repertoire.  Stuns would be nice, but they do carry quite a bit of aggro.  Root would be nice, too.  None of that makes or breaks the class, though.  I will work toward mastery of my class using the tools I have at my disposal.  At high levels, that includes taking full advantage of the AA skills available, the equipment I can get a hold of, and the spells I can cast.  The combination is a sight to behold. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 595<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 7:17:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Really want class balance ?  </span><hr size=1> Some quotes from Prima's strategy book:<br>
<br>
&quot;These masters of summoning are never truly alone...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;With the wiggle of a finger, the Magician can also conjure an array of powerful weapons...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;When it comes to pure damage, the Magician is, throughout most of her career, second only to the Wizard for Direct Damage output.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;While it is true Magicians are one of the best classes to solo (thanks to the combat support of their pets), they also excel in groups.&quot;<br>
<br>
No mention was made of magicians being the master of the elements.  It was, however, mentioned several times that we are the masters of summoning. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A> at: 9/19/02 7:17:31 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujazzen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jazzen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 270<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 10:15:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Really want class balance ?  </span><hr size=1> Do the mage epic quest. It will explain to you all about the class being the true master of the elements. Not the elementals but the very elements. That is why we are able to Manifest the very elements into our orb and harness there power for our own.  Our epic has a cold based dd proc. <br>
<br>
Anyway the mage is a damage class. We are the only class that gets a great pet AND good nukes. Every other pet class lacks instant damage. That is really the major benefit of the mage class. Also back when the class was release/designed the mage PET was designed to be that added damage when we could not nuke mobs. The pet is able to hit what his master can not for the most part.<br>
<br>
My only problem with the mage class is it has not evolved. It isn't growing with expansions. It is for the most part staying the same and VI doesn't know what to do with us. The way to improve the class is to make us powerful at what we currently are powerful at. SUMMONING!!!!<br>
<br>
Give us some wanted summons. Focus items with good stats and procing weapons that someone other then my pet would want. Upgrade to Haste mask and a summoned weapon that procs 25% slow. Something to mitigate damage at least. Every class in the game has grown and expanded I don't see why we can't do the same. I would rather have a weapon that proced 30% slow and summoned focus items that gave +5 to all stats and saves +25hp/mana OVER lures, cold based nukes or root anyday. <br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujochangaladar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 598<br> <font color=#333333>(9/19/02 2:58:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=349.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Really want class balance ?  </span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Do the mage epic quest. It will explain to you all about the class being the true master of the elements. Not the elementals but the very elements. That is why we are able to Manifest the very elements into our orb and harness there power for our own. Our epic has a cold based dd proc.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
