<br>
Walnan:  &quot;I am Walnan, elementalist, summoner, wanderer...&quot;<br>
  &quot;Magi'kot was the most powerful elementalist of his age...  He wished to obtain infinite knowledge and wisdom in order to further expand the arcane art of summoning.&quot;  &quot;The arcane art of Summoning is derived from the power of the elements which surround us.&quot;<br>
<br>
Akkstaff:  &quot;Magi'kot was a powerful elementalist, able to control the power of the elements which surround him.  He was not able to fully master the elements...&quot;<br>
<br>
Rykas:  &quot;An Elementalist's power come sfrom the Orb of Mastery.  The elements of Earth, Fire, Wind, and Water are contained within the orb.  The Master of Elements holds the Orb...  He can be found in the Plane of Air.&quot;<br>
<br>
   Akkstaff's quote is subject to interpretation.  Being able to control the &quot;power&quot; of the elements could simply be an expression for being able to control the minions of the elemental planes.  He didn't literally say elementalists can control the elements.  The only &quot;Master of the Elements&quot; mentioned was the npc in PoA.  Walnan's mention that the art of summoning is derived from the &quot;power&quot; of the elements hints further that our focus is definitely summoning.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> My only problem with the mage class is it has not evolved. It isn't growing with expansions<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
    Our class in not growing and evolving?  I beg to differ.  Pet power has increased since Luclin, with increased damage and max summons being automatic.  Magicians can summon large amounts of mana.  Focus items, dropped and summoned, have increased our power and efficiency.  I remember a lot of posts that were around post-Velious and pre-Luclin complaining about our relative inability to solo in comparison to necromancers, druids, and even wizards.  That's changed, especially with AA skills like Improved Reclaim allowing us to resummon pets virtually mana free.  What used to take me a full mana bar to solo now doesn't even dent it.<br>
<br>
  We are evolving, for certain, especially in the area of summoning.  It would be nice to be able to summon more powerful weapons and armor, items with more cool effects, but we simply don't have them yet.  Hopefully that will change. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
